# Release Workflows

- `publish-package.yml` is a manual dispatch with a `publish` boolean. It must
  publish from the dispatched branch (`main` for v5, `v4.x.x` for legacy
  backports) — do not hardcode a `ref:` that overrides the dispatch.
- `revalidate-sdk-content.yml` and `trigger-sdk-indexer.yml` are post-merge
  hooks on `main` that call external docs systems. Do not trigger or broaden
  them without approval.
- Keep `--no-private`, `--no-verify-access`, and the `PR_BYPASSER` app token
  on the publish job — Lerna pushes the version commit + tag past branch
  protection using that token.
- Keep secrets in GitHub Actions secrets and preserve least-privilege workflow
  permissions.
- Read `.agents/skills/release-workflows/` before changing release automation.
- The legacy `publish-v5-beta.yml` and `update-v5-docs.yml` workflows were
  retired when v5 graduated to `main` on 2026-05-20. Do not resurrect them.
